fields.name: Adirondack 46ers
fields.description: A challenge to hike all 46 of the Adirondack peaks higher than 4000 ft. in elevation. Please note that a few of the mountains are actually a little less than 4000 ft., however this list of 46 mountains has remained as it always was traditionally, before modern and more accurate measurements of elevation were taken. Adirondack Park is a NY State park, and is the largest publicly protected area in the contiguous United States.

fields.name: Catskill 3500
fields.description: Summit each of the 33 peaks in the Catskill range greater than 3500 feet in elevation.

fields.name: North East Ultra 8
fields.description: Eight long and rigorous hikes in the Northeast, and each hike must be completed within a day.

fields.name: New Hampshire 48
fields.description: Hike all 48 New Hampshire peaks greater than 4000 feet in elevation.
